WEBVTT

00:01.029 --> 00:03.063
[Sheep bleats]

00:03.064 --> 00:05.332
[Indistinct conversations]

00:06.233 --> 00:07.400
'Sup?

00:07.401 --> 00:09.702
Hey. Aren't you that guy from the poster?

00:09.703 --> 00:12.570
What? N-no. That's m... that's my cousin.

00:12.572 --> 00:14.172
We got different cheekbones.

00:14.173 --> 00:15.382
His are better, the lucky bastard.

00:15.442 --> 00:17.476
Well, I think it's you.
I'm getting that reward!

00:17.477 --> 00:18.711
Hold on, hold on!

00:18.712 --> 00:20.579
If you hand me over, they'll kill me.

00:20.580 --> 00:22.214
Do you really want my death
on your conscience

00:22.215 --> 00:23.649
for six lousy gold pieces?

00:23.650 --> 00:25.684
What could you even buy with that?

00:25.685 --> 00:26.852
A farm!

00:26.853 --> 00:29.154
I could get a new wife. I hate the old one!

00:29.155 --> 00:31.290
I'm changing mine. I want a new wife, too!

00:31.291 --> 00:32.458
Wait! Please!

00:32.459 --> 00:34.560
Even if you deliver me
to the king and queen,

00:34.561 --> 00:35.828
they'll never pay!

00:35.829 --> 00:38.297
Look what they've done
to this once proud kingdom.

00:38.298 --> 00:41.400
They plundered and destroyed it
and ruined all of our lives!

00:41.401 --> 00:43.569
I mean, where's it written that those jerks

00:43.570 --> 00:45.771
get to live in the castle and feast on lamb

00:45.772 --> 00:48.707
while the rest of us
wallow in the muck and starve?!

00:48.708 --> 00:50.275
Where is it written?

00:50.276 --> 00:51.477
The Kingdom Charter.

00:51.478 --> 00:52.945
Forget where it's written.

00:52.946 --> 00:56.682
I say we storm the castle

00:56.683 --> 00:58.984
and take back what's rightfully ours.

00:58.985 --> 01:00.619
Who's with me?!

01:00.620 --> 01:02.588
[All cheering]

01:02.589 --> 01:05.057
♪ We will march, and we'll fight ♪

01:05.058 --> 01:07.426
♪ For the cause of good and right ♪

01:07.427 --> 01:10.529
♪ Though the odds of us surviving ♪

01:10.530 --> 01:13.332
♪ Are ridiculously slight ♪

01:13.333 --> 01:15.701
♪ And we'll stand proud and tall ♪

01:15.702 --> 01:18.237
♪ Till they come to kill us all ♪

01:18.238 --> 01:21.607
♪ Then we'll beg and plead
and soil ourselves ♪

01:21.608 --> 01:24.042
♪ As, one by one, we fall ♪

01:24.043 --> 01:26.478
♪ Some they'll slash, some they'll hack ♪

01:26.479 --> 01:29.281
♪ Some they'll bludgeon blue and black ♪

01:29.282 --> 01:31.884
♪ Some they'll gut from top to bottom ♪

01:31.885 --> 01:34.353
♪ Some they'll mangle front to back ♪

01:34.354 --> 01:37.322
♪ And we'll all realize ♪

01:37.323 --> 01:40.092
♪ As they're gouging out our eyes ♪

01:40.093 --> 01:42.661
♪ That tomorrow we'll regret it ♪

01:42.662 --> 01:46.898
♪ But today, we rise ♪

01:48.334 --> 01:53.172
♪ And our corpses will rot on the plain ♪

01:53.173 --> 01:58.710
♪ Leaving only a gross, bloody stain ♪

01:58.711 --> 02:01.280
♪ Then the world, it will see ♪

02:01.281 --> 02:04.049
♪ As will all of history ♪

02:04.050 --> 02:06.652
♪ We had truth on our side ♪

02:06.653 --> 02:09.455
♪ But we still died in vain ♪

02:09.455 --> 02:12.024
♪ And the brave, lucky few ♪

02:12.025 --> 02:14.593
♪ Who will somehow make it through ♪

02:14.594 --> 02:16.995
♪ Scarred for life and missing limbs ♪

02:16.996 --> 02:19.731
♪ And needing help to pee and poo ♪

02:19.732 --> 02:22.401
♪ They can stand 'neath these skies ♪

02:22.402 --> 02:25.103
♪ Begging change from passerbys ♪

02:25.104 --> 02:27.840
♪ Is it hopeless? Yep, you said it ♪

02:27.841 --> 02:30.576
♪ We might as well forget it ♪

02:30.577 --> 02:33.045
♪ Tomorrow, we'll regret it ♪

02:33.046 --> 02:35.514
♪ But today, we rise ♪

02:35.515 --> 02:38.350
♪ Oh, my God, will we regret it ♪

02:38.351 --> 02:44.455
♪ But today, we ri-i-i-i-se ♪

02:47.260 --> 02:49.161
Not so tough now, are you?!

02:49.162 --> 02:51.697
We're gonna tear this castle down!

02:51.698 --> 02:53.999
Right, everybody?!

02:54.000 --> 02:56.534
I said, right, everybody?!

02:59.539 --> 03:02.641
Tell me, why do musicals
always get me so worked up?

03:02.642 --> 03:04.967
Galavant - S02E06
About Last Knight

03:04.968 --> 03:06.968
<font color="#00ff80">sync and correction by solfieri
www.addic7ed.com</font>

03:09.878 --> 03:12.113
[Horse grunts]

03:12.114 --> 03:13.481
It stopped.

03:13.482 --> 03:15.082
This is what happened to the last one.

03:15.083 --> 03:16.517
Okay, okay.

03:16.518 --> 03:18.119
Let's just try giving it a kick.

03:18.120 --> 03:19.076
It worked before.

03:19.447 --> 03:21.314
1, 2, 3.

03:21.323 --> 03:22.857
Kick.

03:22.858 --> 03:23.925
Great.

03:23.926 --> 03:25.492
It's useless.

03:26.896 --> 03:28.096
[Grunts]

03:28.097 --> 03:30.131
How could things have gone
so bad so quickly?

03:30.132 --> 03:32.233
Those stupid bats ate all our food.

03:32.234 --> 03:33.735
We all got the same cold.

03:33.736 --> 03:36.037
- Worst of all...
- Please don't say it again.

03:36.038 --> 03:38.373
- We had to eat that family of hobbits.
- Ugh.

03:38.374 --> 03:39.807
Well, we wouldn't have had to

03:39.808 --> 03:41.442
if you'd let us eat your stupid iguana.

03:41.443 --> 03:45.079
Tad Cooper is a dragon,
and we are not eating a dragon.

03:45.080 --> 03:49.017
He's a lizard.
A very sumptuous, meaty lizard.

03:49.018 --> 03:51.386
Richard, look, I'm sorry
we had to eat hobbits.

03:51.387 --> 03:53.488
I'm sorry we'll soon have to
eat your igua...

03:53.489 --> 03:55.290
- [clears throat]
- Dragon.

03:55.291 --> 03:58.126
But we don't have a choice. We're starving.

03:58.127 --> 04:00.528
Hold on a minute.

04:00.529 --> 04:04.799
"Entering the property
of Sir Arnold Galavant."

04:04.800 --> 04:06.000
Huh.

04:06.001 --> 04:08.202
Is he any relation of yours?

04:08.203 --> 04:10.304
Uh...No.

04:14.410 --> 04:15.375
Maybe.

04:17.478 --> 04:19.079
Okay, fine. Yes, he's my dad.

04:19.081 --> 04:21.082
Look, I knew he lived
around here somewhere.

04:21.083 --> 04:22.383
I just don't want to see him.

04:22.384 --> 04:23.685
You knew? We ate hobbits.

04:23.686 --> 04:24.919
Oh, forget about them.

04:24.920 --> 04:27.155
I smell backstory, and I <i> love</i> backstory.

04:27.156 --> 04:28.756
Honestly, I don't want to talk about it.

04:28.757 --> 04:29.991
Can we just move on?

04:29.992 --> 04:31.492
I'm sure we could find
a warm bed and a nice meal

04:31.493 --> 04:33.229
in literally any other direction.

04:33.231 --> 04:35.120
_

04:35.121 --> 04:37.121
_

04:37.122 --> 04:39.122
_

04:40.235 --> 04:42.236
Oh, fiddlesticks.

04:42.237 --> 04:45.139
As you all know,
this is the first birthday party

04:45.140 --> 04:47.775
I've thrown for Gareth
since he became king.

04:47.776 --> 04:49.877
If you ruin the surprise,

04:49.878 --> 04:51.678
I'll cut your tongue out with a dull knife.

04:52.681 --> 04:56.050
Thanks for your hard work,
and I cherish you one and all.

04:56.051 --> 04:57.185
He's coming!

04:57.186 --> 04:58.720
Oh! Places, everyone!

04:58.721 --> 05:00.120
[Giggles]

05:04.960 --> 05:07.061
All: Surprise!

05:07.062 --> 05:08.997
[Grunting]

05:08.998 --> 05:10.598
Gareth! Wait!

05:10.599 --> 05:13.167
It's a birthday party for you,
you kook. [Chuckles]

05:13.168 --> 05:14.636
Oh.

05:14.637 --> 05:16.604
Come take a look at your gifts.

05:16.605 --> 05:18.739
I think you're going to love them.

05:21.243 --> 05:22.510
This is a bit fancy.

05:22.511 --> 05:23.911
It's a crystal nut bowl.

05:23.912 --> 05:25.480
Yeah.

05:25.481 --> 05:26.781
It'll never fit.

05:26.782 --> 05:29.384
No, for dinner parties.

05:29.385 --> 05:30.551
[Clears throat]

05:30.552 --> 05:31.552
Mm.

05:31.553 --> 05:33.121
You don't like it?

05:33.122 --> 05:34.422
It's not that.

05:34.423 --> 05:35.790
It's just that,

05:35.791 --> 05:38.559
all this hoity-toity king stuff...

05:38.560 --> 05:39.961
[Sighs]

05:39.962 --> 05:41.529
It's just not me.

05:41.530 --> 05:44.132
Oh. [Chuckles] Okay.

05:44.133 --> 05:47.935
So, what is you, Gareth?

05:47.936 --> 05:50.371
I mean, if you could get
anything for your birthday,

05:50.372 --> 05:51.773
what would it be?

05:51.774 --> 05:53.240
A scar.

05:54.610 --> 05:56.477
Every year, on my birthday,

05:56.478 --> 05:59.514
we used to go down the pub
and get in a good old scrap.

05:59.515 --> 06:00.882
When I was 9 years old,

06:00.883 --> 06:02.950
I went to the pub and got this one.

06:02.951 --> 06:05.687
Greatest gift a kid could ever want.

06:05.688 --> 06:07.889
This one, I was 14.

06:07.890 --> 06:10.658
I left a man bleeding to death
in the sawdust.

06:10.659 --> 06:13.528
He wanted me to finish him off,
but I wouldn't.

06:13.529 --> 06:16.698
[Laughs]

06:16.699 --> 06:18.299
That's what we're going to do.

06:18.300 --> 06:21.636
I'm taking you to the sleaziest
tavern in Valencia...

06:21.637 --> 06:25.840
To get you a new birthday scar.

06:25.841 --> 06:27.942
Really?

06:27.943 --> 06:30.711
[Fanfare]

06:31.814 --> 06:34.949
[Men grunting]

06:34.950 --> 06:37.685
Where's Wormwood?

06:37.686 --> 06:40.188
My plan is almost ready, Barry.

06:40.189 --> 06:41.622
Your wedding plan?

06:41.623 --> 06:42.857
Yes, and my evil plan.

06:42.858 --> 06:44.459
I thought that was a plot.

06:44.460 --> 06:45.727
Oh, for...

06:45.728 --> 06:48.763
Actually, if I'm being honest,
I'm losing track myself.

06:48.764 --> 06:51.466
[Door opens]

06:51.467 --> 06:54.635
Mr. Wormwood, we need to talk.

06:54.636 --> 06:56.404
[Clears throat]

06:56.405 --> 06:59.207
My lady, there's a perfectly
good explanation.

06:59.208 --> 07:00.842
You were using it to control my mind

07:00.843 --> 07:03.811
and take over our kingdom as
part of some nefarious scheme.

07:03.812 --> 07:05.847
Okay, yes, that is the explanation.

07:05.848 --> 07:07.548
You're lucky I don't have my guards

07:07.549 --> 07:09.050
strike you down just for that.

07:09.051 --> 07:10.785
[Chuckles]

07:10.786 --> 07:14.756
Oh, Princess, I'm a master
of the dark arts, yes.

07:14.757 --> 07:16.858
And the only thing to kill me is the sword

07:16.859 --> 07:19.861
wielded by the one true king
to unite them all.

07:19.862 --> 07:22.530
And no one knows where that is.

07:22.531 --> 07:25.333
Damn it!

07:25.334 --> 07:27.368
There we go.

07:27.369 --> 07:30.471
I can still have them chop off your arms.

07:30.472 --> 07:31.606
Ha!

07:31.607 --> 07:33.207
[Swords unsheathe] Oh.

07:33.208 --> 07:34.742
Can you? Can she?

07:34.743 --> 07:36.344
Yes. Hadn't thought of that.

07:36.345 --> 07:39.413
Begone, Chester Wormwood.

07:39.414 --> 07:42.884
You are banished from Hortensia.

07:42.885 --> 07:43.851
Fine.

07:43.852 --> 07:46.186
You win... for now.

07:47.055 --> 07:48.422
But mark my words,

07:48.423 --> 07:51.726
I will return
to take this kingdom by force,

07:51.727 --> 07:54.796
and you and your family will
decorate my highest tower...

07:54.797 --> 07:56.998
With your heads!

07:56.999 --> 07:59.667
Oh, but don't forget...
The wedding is fast approaching,

07:59.668 --> 08:02.203
so have the groomsmen's gifts
engraved with their initials.

08:02.204 --> 08:04.472
[Smooches] It's a classy move.

08:04.473 --> 08:08.176
But you will die, I swear.

08:08.177 --> 08:10.511
Oh, and don't forget
to tip the waiters on the day.

08:10.512 --> 08:13.014
Oh, they work so hard.

08:13.015 --> 08:16.283
Rot in hell, swine!

08:18.887 --> 08:20.388
Barry.

08:20.389 --> 08:21.823
We're here. Now, look...

08:21.824 --> 08:24.425
Are you sure you wouldn't rather
face starvation?

08:24.426 --> 08:25.660
I would.

08:25.661 --> 08:27.495
You know, I do not understand it.

08:27.496 --> 08:29.530
My father died when I was just a boy.

08:29.531 --> 08:31.632
I would do anything to see him again.

08:31.633 --> 08:32.767
- So hungry.
- Yeah.

08:32.768 --> 08:35.703
Well, your dad probably
wasn't a serial philanderer

08:35.703 --> 08:38.005
who was never around and left your mum.

08:38.006 --> 08:39.307
That is so sad.

08:39.308 --> 08:40.808
Not as sad as having a dead dad, right?

08:40.808 --> 08:42.443
- I mean, my story's sadder.
- Mm.

08:42.443 --> 08:45.179
And just wait until he finds out
I'm on a quest for love.

08:45.180 --> 08:46.981
Oh! He's gonna make such fun of it.

08:46.982 --> 08:48.749
Well, if he criticizes you over dinner,

08:48.750 --> 08:50.318
I'm fine with that,
especially if dinner is steak.

08:50.319 --> 08:51.686
Hear, hear.

08:51.687 --> 08:55.556
Okay. Well, be prepared to meet
an ice-cold, loveless monster.

08:55.557 --> 08:56.657
[Children shouting]

08:56.658 --> 08:59.126
Ha ha ha!

08:59.127 --> 09:01.963
Ah, greetings, son! It's been forever!

09:01.964 --> 09:02.964
Come in.

09:02.965 --> 09:04.832
Oh, yeah. He seems terrible.

09:04.833 --> 09:07.468
Arnold: Boys, make way, make way, make way.

09:07.469 --> 09:09.536
Welcome, welcome.

09:12.724 --> 09:14.758
[Chuckles] I will be damned.

09:14.759 --> 09:18.093
I never thought
I'd live to see my oldest son

09:18.095 --> 09:19.595
with such a bushy beard.

09:19.596 --> 09:22.031
It's not bushy.
It's correct for the period.

09:22.032 --> 09:24.500
And it suits you. Come, come, come.

09:24.501 --> 09:26.536
You have a lovely home, sir.

09:26.537 --> 09:27.637
Thank you.

09:27.638 --> 09:29.005
You have a lot of children.

09:29.006 --> 09:31.007
Your wife must be so sore.

09:31.008 --> 09:32.408
They're not mine.

09:32.409 --> 09:35.311
I run a swordsmanship school
for at-risk youth.

09:35.312 --> 09:38.414
Have been ever since
I retired from the heroics game.

09:38.415 --> 09:39.749
[Grunts]

09:39.750 --> 09:41.117
Hey, boys!

09:41.118 --> 09:42.351
[Boys shouting]

09:42.352 --> 09:44.520
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

09:44.521 --> 09:46.122
One at a time.

09:46.123 --> 09:49.592
Oh, please.

09:49.593 --> 09:52.595
[Patrons cheering]

09:52.596 --> 09:55.797
♪

09:56.233 --> 09:58.134
Man: Kill him!

09:58.135 --> 09:59.167
Crown!

10:00.838 --> 10:04.073
So, how does this whole
bar-fight thing work?

10:04.074 --> 10:06.442
Well, usually, we have a pint or two.

10:06.443 --> 10:08.077
And then I catch someone looking at me,

10:08.078 --> 10:10.847
I insult his mother, and then away we go.

10:10.848 --> 10:12.681
Oh, good. Let's start.

10:15.152 --> 10:16.919
Oh. What about him?

10:16.920 --> 10:19.255
He gave you a momentary glance.

10:19.256 --> 10:20.755
Mm. Did he?

10:22.126 --> 10:23.826
Oy!

10:23.827 --> 10:25.094
You got a problem?

10:25.095 --> 10:27.163
Uh, none at all, uh, Your Highness.

10:27.170 --> 10:28.431
Well, you should.

10:28.432 --> 10:31.400
King Gareth just called
your mother a two-bit hussy.

10:31.401 --> 10:33.169
Oh, uh, right you are, My King!

10:33.170 --> 10:34.337
My mother is a hussy.

10:34.338 --> 10:36.439
In fact, she's the biggest hussy
in the land.

10:36.440 --> 10:38.074
Indeed, I am, your grace!

10:38.075 --> 10:41.077
My mother sells herself,
as well, Your Majesty.

10:41.078 --> 10:42.278
Mine too!

10:42.279 --> 10:44.180
Filthiest woman in
the whole red-candle district.

10:44.181 --> 10:45.381
My <i> father's</i> a hussy!

10:45.382 --> 10:48.083
[All shouting indistinctly]

10:53.323 --> 10:56.792
For God's sake, Barry, try and keep up!

10:56.793 --> 10:59.929
Do you have any idea where we are?

10:59.930 --> 11:02.698
Barry, are you completely illiterate?

11:02.699 --> 11:05.701
Look, we're in the forest of coincidence.

11:05.702 --> 11:09.972
God, I wish we had a cart right now.

11:09.973 --> 11:12.675
Free cart! No way. [Chuckles]

11:12.676 --> 11:15.444
Finally, a stroke of luck.

11:15.445 --> 11:17.680
Ah, hey, you there... Little chap.

11:17.681 --> 11:19.482
Where are you coming from?

11:19.483 --> 11:22.685
Valencia. I'm escaping,
and I couldn't be more lost.

11:22.686 --> 11:24.453
How very strange.

11:24.454 --> 11:26.556
We're escaping from Hortensia.

11:26.557 --> 11:28.758
Hey, maybe we can help each other.

11:28.759 --> 11:29.859
That'd be brilliant.

11:29.860 --> 11:31.994
I'm trying to put as much distance as I can

11:31.995 --> 11:34.230
between myself
and an insane king and queen.

11:34.231 --> 11:36.399
[Chuckles] Believe me, we get that.

11:36.400 --> 11:39.101
We've just been kicked out
by Princess Isabella.

11:39.102 --> 11:40.703
- Princess Isabella?
- Yeah.

11:40.704 --> 11:42.205
She's one of the people I'm looking for.

11:42.206 --> 11:44.040
Really? How incredible.

11:44.041 --> 11:46.442
I'm desperate to find her
and her true love, Galavant.

11:46.443 --> 11:47.777
What are you talking about?

11:47.778 --> 11:49.645
Galavant told her he wished she would die.

11:49.646 --> 11:51.881
In a fart, if I remember correctly.

11:51.882 --> 11:53.816
Galavant never makes fart jokes.

11:53.817 --> 11:55.818
No, it must be a misunderstanding.

11:55.819 --> 11:58.087
I have to find him right away, but how?

11:58.088 --> 11:59.388
Excuse me. Did you say "Galavant"?

11:59.389 --> 12:02.491
Oh, I hear he's staying at his father's place
just a five days' walk away from here.

12:02.492 --> 12:04.760
Oh. And I just found his sword.

12:04.761 --> 12:05.761
Do you want it?

12:05.762 --> 12:07.863
Hell, yeah.

12:07.864 --> 12:10.466
Oh, wow. This is amazing.

12:10.467 --> 12:13.202
If only I had a horse
I could make it by nightfall.

12:13.203 --> 12:15.071
- Man: Horse for sale!
- [Horse whinnies]

12:15.072 --> 12:16.639
Horse for sale!

12:16.640 --> 12:18.908
Take you five days' walk
in a single afternoon.

12:18.909 --> 12:20.743
Oh, my God. That's perfect.

12:20.744 --> 12:22.044
But I have no money.

12:22.045 --> 12:23.246
I don't need money.

12:23.247 --> 12:25.982
What I need is a used pair of size 7 shoes.

12:25.983 --> 12:27.216
I'm a size 7.

12:27.217 --> 12:29.018
And I have an extra pair.

12:29.019 --> 12:30.820
What are the odds?! Let's do this.

12:30.821 --> 12:32.288
[Both laugh]

12:32.289 --> 12:33.688
Yipee!

12:35.459 --> 12:36.759
Good luck to you, friends.

12:36.760 --> 12:38.694
If you're in Valencia, be careful.

12:38.695 --> 12:41.630
The king and queen
are crazy, war-minded monsters.

12:44.601 --> 12:47.103
Crazy, war-minded monsters.

12:47.104 --> 12:48.404
[Chuckles]

12:48.405 --> 12:51.407
What a wonderful coincidence.

12:51.408 --> 12:55.511
All right, boys, who's gonna train me?

12:55.512 --> 12:56.378
Oh.

12:57.748 --> 12:59.048
Oh! Watch the face!

12:59.049 --> 13:00.483
What's wrong with you?

13:00.484 --> 13:02.652
Good Lord.

13:02.653 --> 13:04.587
You know, there was a time
when I would've paid

13:04.588 --> 13:05.621
good money to see this.

13:05.622 --> 13:07.290
It's nice that he's good with kids, though.

13:07.291 --> 13:08.991
Why, you little... [Grunts]

13:08.992 --> 13:10.526
Come here, come here!

13:10.527 --> 13:12.028
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

13:12.029 --> 13:14.397
Galavant, I'm starting to worry
that Richard won't be ready

13:14.398 --> 13:15.531
when the real battle comes.

13:15.532 --> 13:18.000
Careful, Roberta.

13:18.001 --> 13:20.536
You're starting to sound like
someone who cares for the guy.

13:20.537 --> 13:23.772
In love with him? Me? [Scoffs] What?

13:25.042 --> 13:27.643
I'm not in love with him.

13:27.644 --> 13:29.078
What's wrong with you people?!

13:29.079 --> 13:31.146
At all.

13:33.150 --> 13:35.451
Sir Galavant, tell us what it was like

13:35.452 --> 13:37.053
to grow up with your awesome dad.

13:37.054 --> 13:38.788
- Yeah, tell us!
- You're so lucky!

13:38.789 --> 13:40.156
Well, kiddies...

13:40.157 --> 13:41.791
There was this one time...

13:41.792 --> 13:44.393
Well, I remember it like it was yesterday.

13:44.394 --> 13:45.761
Gather 'round.

13:45.762 --> 13:48.130
He told my mother that he didn't love her

13:48.131 --> 13:49.565
right in front of my face.

13:49.566 --> 13:51.334
And then he passed out on the dog.

13:51.335 --> 13:54.737
And it was Christmas, and the dog died.

13:54.738 --> 14:00.576
That man doesn't care
about anybody but himself.

14:00.577 --> 14:01.810
That's not true.

14:03.647 --> 14:05.348
♪ I was starving in the poorhouse ♪

14:05.349 --> 14:07.083
♪ Where they fed us twice a year ♪

14:07.084 --> 14:09.552
♪ And they tossed me out
the day I asked for more ♪

14:09.553 --> 14:10.686
Aw.

14:10.687 --> 14:12.121
♪ Then your dad brought me to your house ♪

14:12.122 --> 14:13.789
♪ And he gave me bread and beer ♪

14:13.790 --> 14:16.525
♪ Also, everything you left here
in your drawer ♪

14:16.526 --> 14:17.560
Wait. What?

14:17.561 --> 14:18.728
♪ He was there, he was there ♪

14:18.729 --> 14:20.529
♪ Gave me all your underwear ♪

14:20.530 --> 14:23.599
♪ With his sweet, loving care,
he was there ♪

14:23.600 --> 14:25.567
You've got to be kidding me.

14:27.104 --> 14:28.771
♪ I was carried off by slavers ♪

14:28.772 --> 14:30.539
♪ Where my parents died of pox ♪

14:30.540 --> 14:33.042
♪ And they sold me
to be rendered into glue ♪

14:33.043 --> 14:34.176
Ew!

14:34.177 --> 14:35.511
♪ Then your dad did me two favors ♪

14:35.512 --> 14:37.012
♪ First, he cleaned their freaking clocks ♪

14:37.013 --> 14:39.648
♪ Then he gave me all the gear
he gave to you ♪

14:39.649 --> 14:40.950
Hey, that's my favorite hat!

14:40.951 --> 14:42.184
♪ He was there, he was there ♪

14:42.185 --> 14:43.919
♪ Random back-flip in the air ♪

14:43.920 --> 14:45.421
- All: Yay!
- ♪ So much more ♪

14:45.422 --> 14:46.255
- ♪ Love to spare ♪
- ♪ Love to spare ♪

14:46.256 --> 14:47.156
♪ Such a gem ♪

14:47.157 --> 14:48.391
- ♪ Such a... ♪
- Stop!

14:48.392 --> 14:49.759
♪ I was practically abandoned ♪

14:49.760 --> 14:51.527
♪ By that smug and selfish jerk ♪

14:51.528 --> 14:53.963
♪ It's like nothing that I did
was quite enough ♪

14:53.964 --> 14:54.964
That's rough.

14:54.965 --> 14:56.599
♪ Plus, his ego's out of hand ♪

14:56.600 --> 14:58.267
♪ And all he cares about is work ♪

14:58.268 --> 15:00.536
♪ And I can't believe
he gave you all my stuff ♪

15:00.537 --> 15:01.670
What?! No!

15:01.671 --> 15:03.572
- ♪ He was there ♪
- ♪ Never there ♪

15:03.573 --> 15:05.074
- ♪ He was... ♪
 - ♪ Mever, ever there ♪

15:05.075 --> 15:06.809
- ♪ Sweet and kind ♪
- ♪ Au contraire ♪

15:06.810 --> 15:09.011
- ♪ He's a Saint ♪
- ♪ Not a prayer ♪

15:09.012 --> 15:10.346
♪ Nasty and cold-hearted ♪

15:10.347 --> 15:11.981
♪ Such a pig, don't get me started ♪

15:11.982 --> 15:13.716
♪ He's a schmuck, he's a schmo ♪

15:13.717 --> 15:15.484
♪ He's the worst, I should know ♪

15:15.485 --> 15:18.621
♪ He's my dad, he's a cad ♪

15:18.622 --> 15:21.322
[Sighs] He's right behind me, isn't he?

15:27.019 --> 15:29.253
Mama! Dad.

15:29.254 --> 15:30.755
You look terrible.

15:30.756 --> 15:32.657
Because you threw us in the dungeon.

15:33.059 --> 15:34.959
I know. And I'm so sorry.

15:34.959 --> 15:36.627
But it wasn't me. It was a spell.

15:36.628 --> 15:38.462
We slept in an inch of water.

15:38.463 --> 15:40.697
I have mold in the crack of my tuchus.

15:40.698 --> 15:42.399
Todd, enough.

15:42.400 --> 15:46.236
Isabella, we owe you an apology.

15:46.237 --> 15:49.039
We tried to force you
to be somebody you weren't.

15:49.040 --> 15:50.941
And we are sorry.

15:50.942 --> 15:52.743
Sorry.

15:52.744 --> 15:54.211
Oh, thank you.

15:54.212 --> 15:55.446
My baby.

15:55.447 --> 15:58.148
And now it's over, forever,

15:58.149 --> 16:00.117
because I am so done with being controlled

16:00.118 --> 16:01.985
by my broken heart and Prince Harry.

16:01.986 --> 16:04.922
And I'm ready to become my own person.

16:04.923 --> 16:08.058
Let's do this.

16:08.059 --> 16:09.560
Let us begin.

16:09.561 --> 16:13.597
Typically, and by kingdom charter,

16:13.598 --> 16:16.266
when a princess breaks off
her engagement with the prince,

16:16.267 --> 16:18.535
- it requires one simple action.
- Great.

16:18.536 --> 16:20.671
He demands your bra.

16:20.672 --> 16:22.639
My... my bra?

16:22.640 --> 16:24.741
Your bra... To show to my friends.

16:24.742 --> 16:26.543
Absolutely not!

16:26.544 --> 16:27.811
I am a liberated woman.

16:27.812 --> 16:29.113
I am a warrior princess,

16:29.114 --> 16:32.316
and I will not be giving
an 11-year-old my bra.

16:32.317 --> 16:33.951
Then death it is.

16:33.952 --> 16:36.253
[Sighs] Fine.

16:36.254 --> 16:37.621
Unbelievable.

16:37.622 --> 16:39.289
But I am lobbying to change this law.

16:39.290 --> 16:40.591
Yes!

16:40.592 --> 16:43.593
♪

16:47.432 --> 16:48.732
This is me.

16:48.733 --> 16:50.099
It is.

16:51.202 --> 16:53.937
I stitched it. It's your whole life.

16:53.938 --> 16:55.538
There's you when you were born.

16:57.709 --> 17:00.611
That's you being fitted for
your first suit of chain mail.

17:00.612 --> 17:03.547
Yeah, I remember that.
The blacksmith was all hands.

17:03.548 --> 17:05.315
Yeah, you can see it right there.

17:05.316 --> 17:07.317
And that's you, waiting for me to play

17:07.318 --> 17:09.051
"Throw the Cabbage Around"...

17:09.053 --> 17:11.922
When I forgot and never showed.

17:11.923 --> 17:13.290
You're kidding.

17:13.290 --> 17:15.058
That's the day I won the M.V.K.

17:15.059 --> 17:16.926
At the St. Julian's day massacre.

17:16.928 --> 17:18.829
Most valuable knight.

17:18.829 --> 17:21.865
You ripped those serfs to pieces.

17:21.866 --> 17:25.969
You couldn't know how proud I was that day.

17:25.970 --> 17:27.671
Mostly because I didn't tell you.

17:27.672 --> 17:30.806
You've been following
my adventures this whole time.

17:32.744 --> 17:34.678
Why didn't you say anything?

17:34.679 --> 17:38.315
You know us old-school knights.

17:38.316 --> 17:42.486
We can really only express
ourselves through tapestry.

17:42.487 --> 17:45.155
♪

17:45.156 --> 17:46.690
♪ I went mucking all about ♪

17:46.691 --> 17:49.993
♪ On endless quests and empty wars ♪

17:49.994 --> 17:54.097
♪ And adventures
in a hundred ports of call ♪

17:54.098 --> 17:57.401
♪ And yet somehow I missed out
on one adventure ♪

17:57.402 --> 18:00.037
♪ Mine and yours ♪

18:00.038 --> 18:04.140
♪ And it should have been
the greatest one of all ♪

18:05.510 --> 18:07.777
But there's something you should know.

18:10.248 --> 18:13.684
♪ I was there, I was there ♪

18:13.685 --> 18:16.687
♪ In my heart, in every prayer ♪

18:16.688 --> 18:19.089
♪ Never said it out loud ♪

18:19.090 --> 18:22.125
♪ But I've always been proud ♪

18:22.126 --> 18:26.263
♪ If you somehow can forgive me ♪

18:26.264 --> 18:30.267
♪ I'll be ♪

18:30.268 --> 18:33.202
♪ There ♪

18:37.275 --> 18:40.043
Go and rescue your princess, Galavant.

18:40.044 --> 18:43.213
Marry her.

18:43.214 --> 18:47.216
And be the father and husband I never was.

18:49.988 --> 18:51.587
Dad?

18:53.424 --> 18:54.957
You want to play Throw the Cabbage Around?

18:56.628 --> 18:57.893
Grab a head.

